# Project conventions

- **Scope:** Change only what the task requires. No drive-by refactors, no unrelated files, no unsolicited documentation or new markdown unless the user asks.
- **Execution:** Prefer running commands (install, build, lint, dev server) in this environment rather than only suggesting them.
- **Style:** Match existing naming, imports, component structure, and formatting in files you touch. Extend existing helpers (`drawMeme`, handlers) instead of duplicating logic.
- **UI theme:** Primary accent is teal; avoid blue/purple as the main brand color. Keep orange/green handle accents aligned with `src/App.css` and `src/index.css`.
- **References:** When pointing at code in chat, use fenced code citations with path and line range as required by the editor.
